cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.PM, cs.ARCH, cs.SYSCONF

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on analyzing the microarchitecture of Intel's Haswell processor, which falls under the category of computer architecture. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper uses a diagnostic performance model and microbenchmarks to quantify the efficiency of the microarchitecture, which is related to performance analysis. 
- cs.PM (Programming Languages): The paper discusses improvements in the memory hierarchy, which is relevant to programming languages and memory management. 
- cs.ARCH (Computer Architecture): Similar to cs.AR, this category is relevant because the paper analyzes the microarchitecture of a processor. 
- cs.SYSCONF (Systems and Control): The paper discusses features such as Uncore Frequency Scaling and Cluster-on-Die mode, which are related to system-level control and configuration.
